The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Bhel boilers for nuclear power units

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

 Chennai, Aug. 3: Bharat Heavy Electricals Ltds (Bhel) heavy pressure boiler plant in Tiruchirapalli will offer 1000-mw and 800-mw super critical boilers, besides a 700-mw power generating equipment, for nuclear power plants.

 So far, Bhel has been making boilers for power stations with capacities up to 500 mw.

 Orders were expected for its products this year itself, Bhels director (power) K. Ravikumar said at a customers meet in Chennai organised by the Tiruchirapalli unit.

 Ravikumar said Bhel was also working on improving the heat rate of turbines and the coal burning efficiency of boilers of 500-mw units. 

 Officials from different power utilities participated in the meeting. 

 Bhel would increase its production capacity to 10,000 mw a year by March 2007, he added. 




